  "local_port": 37054,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are best computer games?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" computer games can vary greatly depending on individual preferences, such as favored genres, playstyles, and storytelling elements. However, several titles have consistently received critical acclaim and have amassed large, dedicated fanbases due to their exceptional gameplay, storytelling, graphics, and innovation. Below is a curated list of some of the best computer games across various genres as of 2023:\n\n---\n\n### **Action/Adventure**\n\n1. **The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Offers a vast open world filled with rich storytelling, complex characters, and meaningful choices that impact the game\u2019s outcome. Its expansive quests and stunning visuals set a high standard for RPGs.\n\n2. **Red Dead Redemption 2**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Combines an immersive narrative with a beautifully crafted open-world environment set in the Wild West. Its attention to detail and character development provide a deeply engaging experience.\n\n3. **Hades**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A roguelike dungeon crawler that blends fast-paced combat with a compelling narrative. Its innovative storytelling through repeated runs and character interactions makes each playthrough unique.\n\n---\n\n### **Role-Playing Games (RPGs)**\n\n1. **Elden Ring**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Developed by FromSoftware, it blends challenging gameplay with a sprawling open-world setting. Its intricate lore and freedom in exploration offer a deeply rewarding experience for RPG enthusiasts.\n\n2. **Divinity: Original Sin 2**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Known for its deep tactical combat, rich storytelling, and expansive character customization. It also supports cooperative multiplayer, making it a favorite for both solo and group play.\n\n3. **Cyberpunk 2077**\n   - **Why It's Great:** After significant updates, it provides a detailed and immersive open-world experience set in a dystopian future. Its complex narrative and character customization options appeal to many RPG fans.\n\n---\n\n### **Strategy**\n\n1. **Civilization VI**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A turn-based strategy game where players build and expand their civilization through the ages. Its strategic depth and replayability make it a staple for strategy enthusiasts.\n\n2. **StarCraft II**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A real-time strategy game renowned for its competitive multiplayer scene and engaging campaigns. Its balanced gameplay and strategic complexity have kept it popular for years.\n\n3. **Total War: Warhammer III**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Combines real-time battles with turn-based strategy elements in a rich fantasy setting. Its expansive campaign and diverse factions offer endless strategic possibilities.\n\n---\n\n### **First-Person Shooters (FPS)**\n\n1. **Doom Eternal**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Known for its fast-paced, visceral combat and intense action sequences. Its fluid movement system and aggressive gameplay set it apart in the FPS genre.\n\n2. **Half-Life: Alyx**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A VR-exclusive title that has been praised for its immersive storytelling and innovative gameplay mechanics. It's considered a milestone in virtual reality gaming.\n\n3. **Valorant**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A tactical shooter that emphasizes team-based gameplay and strategic planning. Its blend of precise shooting mechanics and unique character abilities has made it a favorite in competitive gaming circles.\n\n---\n\n### **Simulation**\n\n1. **Microsoft Flight Simulator (2020)**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Offers highly realistic flight simulation with stunning graphics and accurate global mapping. Its attention to detail provides an authentic flying experience for enthusiasts and casual players alike.\n\n2. **The Sims 4**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A life simulation game that allows players to create and manage virtual people and their lives. Its extensive customization options and creative freedom have made it a long-standing favorite.\n\n3. **Stardew Valley**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A farming simulation game with RPG elements. Its relaxing gameplay, charming graphics, and depth of content make it appealing to a wide range of players.\n\n---\n\n### **Indie Games**\n\n1. **Hollow Knight**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A beautifully crafted metroidvania with challenging gameplay and an atmospheric world. Its intricate level design and compelling story have garnered a dedicated fanbase.\n\n2. **Celeste**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A platformer that combines precise controls with a heartfelt narrative about overcoming personal challenges. Its challenging levels and emotional depth make it a standout indie title.\n\n3. **Undertale**\n   - **Why It's Great:** An RPG known for its unique storytelling, memorable characters, and innovative gameplay mechanics. Its ability to subvert traditional game tropes has earned it widespread acclaim.\n\n---\n\n### **Multiplayer/Online**\n\n1. **Minecraft**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A sandbox game that offers endless possibilities for building, exploration, and multiplayer collaboration. Its simple yet profound gameplay mechanics have made it one of the best-selling games of all time.\n\n2. **League of Legends**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A highly popular multiplayer online battle arena (MOBA) game known for its competitive scene, diverse character roster, and strategic depth.\n\n3. **Among Us**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A social deduction game that has gained massive popularity for its engaging multiplayer interactions and accessible gameplay, making it a favorite for casual and party gaming.\n\n---\n\n### **Narrative-Driven**\n\n1. **Disco Elysium**\n   - **Why It's Great:** An RPG that emphasizes dialogue and character development over combat. Its deep narrative and complex characters offer a unique and engaging storytelling experience.\n\n2. **Life is Strange Series**\n   - **Why It's Great:** Episodic adventure games with strong narratives and player-driven choices. Each installment offers emotionally impactful stories that resonate with players.\n\n3. **The Last of Us Part I**\n   - **Why It's Great:** A story-driven action-adventure game known for its emotional narrative, character development, and immersive world-building.\n\n---\n\n### **Honorable Mentions**\n\n- **Grand Theft Auto V** \u2013 Open-world action-adventure with endless content and multiplayer options.\n- **Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice** \u2013 Challenging action-adventure game with precise combat mechanics.\n- **Portal 2** \u2013 Puzzle-platformer celebrated for its innovative mechanics and witty writing.\n- **Overwatch** \u2013 Team-based shooter with diverse characters and dynamic gameplay.\n- **Resident Evil Village** \u2013 Survival horror game known for its atmospheric tension and compelling story.\n\n---\n\n### **Upcoming Titles (As of 2023)**\n\n1. **Starfield**\n   - **Why It's Anticipated:** An ambitious RPG from Bethesda set in space, promising extensive exploration and deep storytelling.\n\n2. **The Elder Scrolls VI**\n   - **Why It's Anticipated:** The next installment in the beloved Elder Scrolls series, expected to bring new adventures and innovations to the franchise.\n\n3. **Hogwarts Legacy**\n   - **Why It's Anticipated:** An open-world action RPG set in the Harry Potter universe, allowing players to experience life as a student at Hogwarts with rich lore and magical gameplay.\n\n---\n\n### **Choosing the Right Game for You**\n\nThe \"best\" computer game ultimately depends on what you're looking for in terms of experience. Whether you prefer deep storytelling, competitive multiplayer, strategic planning, or creative freedom, there's a game out there that can provide an exceptional experience. Exploring different genres and reading reviews can help you find the games that best match your interests.\n\n---\n\nFeel free to ask for more specific recommendations based on particular genres or features you're interested in!",
